NOTE: This property is stored in XMP as xmp:ModifyDate.
Xmp.tiff.DateTime.label: Date and Time

Xmp.tiff.ImageDescription.desc: TIFF tag 270, 0x10E. Description of the image. Note: This property is stored in XMP as dc:description.
Xmp.tiff.ImageDescription.label: Image Description

Xmp.tiff.Make.desc: TIFF tag 271, 0x10F. Manufacturer of recording equipment.
Xmp.tiff.Make.label: Make

Xmp.tiff.Model.desc: TIFF tag 272, 0x110. Model name or number of equipment.
Xmp.tiff.Model.label: Model

Xmp.tiff.Software.desc: TIFF tag 305, 0x131. Software or firmware used to generate image. Note: This property is stored in XMP as xmp:CreatorTool.
Xmp.tiff.Software.label: Software

Xmp.tiff.Artist.desc: TIFF tag 315, 0x13B. Camera owner, photographer or image creator. Note: This property is stored in XMP as the first item in the dc:creator array.

Xmp.tiff.Copyright.desc: TIFF tag 33432, 0x8298. Copyright information. Note: This property is stored in XMP as dc:rights.
Xmp.tiff.Copyright.label: Copyright

Xmp.crs.ChromaticAberrationB.desc: "Chromatic Aberration, Fix Blue/Yellow Fringe" setting. Range -100 to +100.
Xmp.crs.ChromaticAberrationB.label: Chromatic Aberration Blue

Xmp.crs.ChromaticAberrationR.desc: "Chromatic Aberration, Fix Red/Cyan Fringe" setting. Range -100 to +100.
Xmp.crs.ChromaticAberrationR.label: Chromatic Aberration Red

Xmp.crs.CropTop.desc: When "Has Crop" is true, top of crop rectangle
Xmp.crs.CropTop.label: Crop Top

Xmp.crs.CropLeft.desc: When "Has Crop" is true, left of crop rectangle.
Xmp.crs.CropLeft.label: Crop Left

Xmp.crs.CropBottom.desc: When "Has Crop" is true, bottom of crop rectangle.
Xmp.crs.CropBottom.label: Crop Bottom

Xmp.crs.CropRight.desc: When "Has Crop" is true, right of crop rectangle.
Xmp.crs.CropRight.label: Crop Right

Xmp.crs.CropAngle.desc: When "Has Crop" is true, angle of crop rectangle.
Xmp.crs.CropAngle.label: Crop Angle

Xmp.crs.CropWidth.desc: Width of resulting cropped image in CropUnits units.
Xmp.crs.CropWidth.label: Crop Width

Xmp.crs.CropHeight.desc: Height of resulting cropped image in CropUnits units.
Xmp.crs.CropHeight.label: Crop Height

Xmp.crs.HasCrop.desc: When true, image has a cropping rectangle.
Xmp.crs.HasCrop.label: Has Crop

Xmp.crs.HasSettings.desc: When true, non-default camera raw settings.
Xmp.crs.HasSettings.label: Has Settings

Xmp.crs.RawFileName.desc: File name of raw file (not a complete path).
Xmp.crs.RawFileName.label: Raw File Name

Xmp.crs.ToneCurve.desc: Array of points (Integer, Integer) defining a "Tone Curve".
Xmp.crs.ToneCurve.label: Tone Curve

Xmp.crs.ToneCurveName.desc: The name of the Tone Curve described by ToneCurve. One of: Linear, Medium Contrast, Strong Contrast, Custom or a user-defined preset name.
Xmp.crs.ToneCurveName.label: Tone Curve Name

Xmp.crs.WhiteBalance.desc: "White Balance" setting. One of: As Shot, Auto, Daylight, Cloudy, Shade, Tungsten, Fluorescent, Flash, Custom
Xmp.crs.WhiteBalance.label: White Balance

Xmp.photoshop.DateCreated.desc: The date the intellectual content of the document was created (rather than the creation date of the physical representation), following IIM conventions. For example, a photo taken during the American Civil War would have a creation date during that epoch (1861-1865) rather than the date the photo was digitized for archiving.
Xmp.photoshop.DateCreated.label: Date Created

Xmp.pdf.PDFVersion.desc: The PDF file version (for example: 1.0, 1.3, and so on).
Xmp.pdf.PDFVersion.label: PDF Version

Xmp.pdf.Producer.desc: The name of the tool that created the PDF document.
Xmp.pdf.Producer.label: Producer

Xmp.xmpDM.projectRef.desc: A reference to the project that created this file.
Xmp.xmpDM.projectRef.label: Project Reference

Xmp.xmpDM.videoFrameRate.desc: The video frame rate. One of: 24, NTSC, PAL.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoFrameRate.label: Video Frame Rate

Xmp.xmpDM.videoFrameSize.desc: The frame size. For example: w:720, h: 480, unit:pixels
Xmp.xmpDM.videoFrameSize.label: Video Frame Size

Xmp.xmpDM.videoPixelAspectRatio.desc: The aspect ratio, expressed as ht/wd. For example: "648/720" = 0.9
Xmp.xmpDM.videoPixelAspectRatio.label: Video Pixel Aspect Ratio

Xmp.xmpDM.videoPixelDepth.desc: The size in bits of each color component of a pixel. Standard Windows 32-bit pixels have 8 bits per component. One of: 8Int, 16Int, 32Int, 32Float.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoPixelDepth.label: Video Pixel Depth

Xmp.xmpDM.videoColorSpace.desc: The color space. One of: sRGB (used by Photoshop), CCIR-601 (used for NTSC), CCIR-709 (used for HD).
Xmp.xmpDM.videoColorSpace.label: Video Color Space

Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaMode.desc: The alpha mode. One of: straight, pre-multiplied.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaMode.label: Video Alpha Mode

Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaPremultipleColor.desc: A color in CMYK or RGB to be used as the pre-multiple color when alpha mode is pre-multiplied.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaPremultipleColor.label: Video Alpha Premultiple Color

Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaUnityIsTransparent.desc: When true, unity is clear, when false, it is opaque.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoAlphaUnityIsTransparent.label: Video Alpha Unity Is Transparent

Xmp.xmpDM.videoCompressor.desc: Video compression used. For example, jpeg.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoCompressor.label: Video Compressor

Xmp.xmpDM.videoFieldOrder.desc: The field order for video. One of: Upper, Lower, Progressive.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoFieldOrder.label: Video Field Order

Xmp.xmpDM.pullDown.desc: The sampling phase of film to be converted to video (pull-down). One of: WSSWW, SSWWW, SWWWS, WWWSS, WWSSW, WSSWW_24p, SSWWW_24p, SWWWS_24p, WWWSS_24p, WWSSW_24p.
Xmp.xmpDM.pullDown.label: Pull Down

Xmp.xmpDM.audioSampleRate.desc: The audio sample rate. Can be any value, but commonly 32000, 41100, or 48000.
Xmp.xmpDM.audioSampleRate.label: Audio Sample Rate

Xmp.xmpDM.audioSampleType.desc: The audio sample type. One of: 8Int, 16Int, 32Int, 32Float.
Xmp.xmpDM.audioSampleType.label: Audio Sample Type

Xmp.xmpDM.audioChannelType.desc: The audio channel type. One of: Mono, Stereo, 5.1, 7.1.
Xmp.xmpDM.audioChannelType.label: Audio Channel Type

Xmp.xmpDM.audioCompressor.desc: The audio compression used. For example, MP3.
Xmp.xmpDM.audioCompressor.label: Audio Compressor

Xmp.xmpDM.speakerPlacement.desc: A description of the speaker angles from center front in degrees. For example: "Left = -30, Right = 30, Center = 0, LFE = 45, Left Surround = -110, Right Surround = 110"
Xmp.xmpDM.speakerPlacement.label: Speaker Placement

Xmp.xmpDM.fileDataRate.desc: The file data rate in megabytes per second. For example: "36/10" = 3.6 MB/sec
Xmp.xmpDM.fileDataRate.label: File Data Rate

Xmp.xmpDM.tapeName.desc: The name of the tape from which the clip was captured, as set during the capture process.
Xmp.xmpDM.tapeName.label: Tape Name

Xmp.xmpDM.altTapeName.desc: An alternative tape name, set via the project window or timecode dialog in Premiere. If an alternative name has been set and has not been reverted, that name is displayed.
Xmp.xmpDM.altTapeName.label: Alternative Tape Name

Xmp.xmpDM.startTimecode.desc: The timecode of the first frame of video in the file, as obtained from the device control.
Xmp.xmpDM.startTimecode.label: Start Time Code

Xmp.xmpDM.altTimecode.desc: A timecode set by the user. When specified, it is used instead of the startTimecode.
Xmp.xmpDM.altTimecode.label: Alternative Time code

Xmp.xmpDM.duration.desc: The duration of the media file.
Xmp.xmpDM.duration.label: Duration

Xmp.xmpDM.shotName.desc: The name of the shot or take.
Xmp.xmpDM.shotName.label: Shot Name

Xmp.xmpDM.shotDate.desc: The date and time when the video was shot.
Xmp.xmpDM.shotDate.label: Shot Date

Xmp.xmpDM.shotLocation.desc: The name of the location where the video was shot. For example: "Oktoberfest, Munich Germany" For more accurate positioning, use the EXIF GPS values.
Xmp.xmpDM.shotLocation.label: Shot Location

Xmp.xmpDM.contributedMedia.desc: An unordered list of all media used to create this media.
Xmp.xmpDM.contributedMedia.label: Contributed Media

Xmp.xmpDM.absPeakAudioFilePath.desc: The absolute path to the file's peak audio file. If empty, no peak file exists.
Xmp.xmpDM.absPeakAudioFilePath.label: Absolute Peak Audio File Path

Xmp.xmpDM.relativePeakAudioFilePath.desc: The relative path to the file's peak audio file. If empty, no peak file exists.
Xmp.xmpDM.relativePeakAudioFilePath.label: Relative Peak Audio File Path

Xmp.xmpDM.videoModDate.desc: The date and time when the video was last modified.
Xmp.xmpDM.videoModDate.label: Video Modified Date

Xmp.xmpDM.audioModDate.desc: The date and time when the audio was last modified.
Xmp.xmpDM.audioModDate.label: Audio Modified Date

Xmp.xmpDM.metadataModDate.desc: The date and time when the metadata was last modified.
Xmp.xmpDM.metadataModDate.label: Metadata Modified Date

Xmp.xmpDM.artist.desc: The name of the artist or artists.
Xmp.xmpDM.artist.label: Artist

Xmp.xmpDM.trackNumber.desc: A numeric value indicating the order of the audio file within its original recording.
Xmp.xmpDM.trackNumber.label: Track Number

Xmp.xmpDM.releaseDate.desc: The date the title was released.
Xmp.xmpDM.releaseDate.label: Release Date

Xmp.xmpDM.introTime.desc: The duration of lead time for queuing music.
Xmp.xmpDM.introTime.label: Intro Time

Xmp.xmpDM.outCue.desc: The time at which to fade out.
Xmp.xmpDM.outCue.label: Out Cue

Xmp.xmpDM.relativeTimestamp.desc: The start time of the media inside the audio project.
Xmp.xmpDM.relativeTimestamp.label: Relative Timestamp

Xmp.xmpDM.loop.desc: When true, the clip can be looped seemlessly.
Xmp.xmpDM.loop.label: Loop

Xmp.xmpDM.key.desc: The audio's musical key. One of: C, C#, D, D#, E, F, F#, G, G#, A, A#, B.
Xmp.xmpDM.key.label: Key

Xmp.xmpDM.stretchMode.desc: The audio stretch mode. One of: Fixed length, Time-Scale, Resample, Beat Splice, Hybrid.
Xmp.xmpDM.stretchMode.label: Stretch Mode

Xmp.xmpDM.timeScaleParams.desc: Additional parameters for Time-Scale stretch mode.
Xmp.xmpDM.timeScaleParams.label: Time Scale Parameters

Xmp.xmpDM.resampleParams.desc: Additional parameters for Resample stretch mode.
Xmp.xmpDM.resampleParams.label: Resample Parameters

Xmp.xmpDM.beatSpliceParams.desc: Additional parameters for Beat Splice stretch mode.
Xmp.xmpDM.beatSpliceParams.label: Beat Splice Parameters

Xmp.xmpDM.timeSignature.desc: The time signature of the music. One of: 2/4, 3/4, 4/4, 5/4, 7/4, 6/8, 9/8, 12/8, other.
Xmp.xmpDM.timeSignature.label: Time Signature

Xmp.xmpDM.scaleType.desc: The musical scale used in the music. One of: Major, Minor, Both, Neither. Neither is most often used for instruments with no associated scale, such as drums.
Xmp.xmpDM.scaleType.label: Scale Type

Xmp.xmpTPg.MaxPageSize.desc: The size of the largest page in the document (including any in contained documents).
Xmp.xmpTPg.MaxPageSize.label: Maximum Page Size

Xmp.xmpTPg.NPages.desc: The number of pages in the document (including any in contained documents).
Xmp.xmpTPg.NPages.label: Number of Pages

Xmp.xmpTPg.Fonts.desc: An unordered array of fonts that are used in the document (including any in contained documents).
Xmp.xmpTPg.Fonts.label: Fonts

Xmp.xmpTPg.Colorants.desc: An ordered array of colorants (swatches) that are used in the document (including any in contained documents).
Xmp.xmpTPg.Colorants.label: Colorants

Xmp.xmpTPg.PlateNames.desc: An ordered array of plate names that are needed to print the document (including any in contained documents).
Xmp.xmpTPg.PlateNames.label: Plate Names

Xmp.xmpBJ.JobRef.desc: References an external job management file for a job process in which the document is being used. Use of job names is under user control. Typical use would be to identify all documents that are part of a particular job or contract. There are multiple values because there can be more than one job using a particular document at any time, and it can also be useful to keep historical information about what jobs a document was part of previously.
Xmp.xmpBJ.JobRef.label: Job Reference

Xmp.xmpMM.DerivedFrom.desc: A reference to the original document from which this one is derived. It is a minimal reference; missing components can be assumed to be unchanged. For example, a new version might only need to specify the instance ID and version number of the previous version, or a rendition might only need to specify the instance ID and rendition class of the original.
Xmp.xmpMM.DerivedFrom.label: Derived From

Xmp.xmpMM.DocumentID.desc: The common identifier for all versions and renditions of a document. It should be based on a UUID; see Document and Instance IDs below.
Xmp.xmpMM.DocumentID.label: Document ID

Xmp.xmpMM.History.desc: An ordered array of high-level user actions that resulted in this resource. It is intended to give human readers a general indication of the steps taken to make the changes from the previous version to this one. The list should be at an abstract level; it is not intended to be an exhaustive keystroke or other detailed history.
Xmp.xmpMM.History.label: History

Xmp.xmpMM.InstanceID.desc: An identifier for a specific incarnation of a document, updated each time a file is saved. It should be based on a UUID; see Document and Instance IDs below.
Xmp.xmpMM.InstanceID.label: Instance ID

Xmp.xmpMM.ManagedFrom.desc: A reference to the document as it was prior to becoming managed. It is set when a managed document is introduced to an asset management system that does not currently own it. It may or may not include references to different management systems.
Xmp.xmpMM.ManagedFrom.label: Managed From

Xmp.xmpMM.Manager.desc: The name of the asset management system that manages this resource. Along with xmpMM: ManagerVariant, it tells applications which asset management system to contact concerning this document.
Xmp.xmpMM.Manager.label: Manager

Xmp.xmpMM.ManageTo.desc: A URI identifying the managed resource to the asset management system; the presence of this property is the formal indication that this resource is managed. The form and content of this URI is private to the asset management system.
Xmp.xmpMM.ManageTo.label: Manage To

Xmp.xmpMM.ManageUI.desc: A URI that can be used to access information about the managed resource through a web browser. It might require a custom browser plug-in.
Xmp.xmpMM.ManageUI.label: Manage UI

Xmp.xmpMM.ManagerVariant.desc: Specifies a particular variant of the asset management system. The format of this property is private to the specific asset management system.
Xmp.xmpMM.ManagerVariant.label: Manager Variant

Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionClass.desc: The rendition class name for this resource. This property should be absent or set to default for a document version that is not a derived rendition.
Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionClass.label: Rendition Class

Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionParams.desc: Can be used to provide additional rendition parameters that are too complex or verbose to encode in xmpMM: RenditionClass.
Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionParams.label: Rendition Params

Xmp.xmpMM.VersionID.desc: The document version identifier for this resource. Each version of a document gets a new identifier, usually simply by incrementing integers 1, 2, 3 . . . and so on. Media management systems can have other conventions or support branching which requires a more complex scheme.
Xmp.xmpMM.VersionID.label: Version ID

Xmp.xmpMM.Versions.desc: The version history associated with this resource. Entry [1] is the oldest known version for this document, entry [last()] is the most recent version. Typically, a media management system would fill in the version information in the metadata on check-in. It is not guaranteed that a complete history versions from the first to this one will be present in the xmpMM:Versions property. Interior version information can be compressed or eliminated and the version history can be truncated at some point.
Xmp.xmpMM.Versions.label: Versions

Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionOf.desc: Deprecated in favor of xmpMM:DerivedFrom. A reference to the document of which this is a rendition.
Xmp.xmpMM.RenditionOf.label: Rendition Of

Xmp.xmpMM.SaveID.desc: Deprecated. Previously used only to support the xmpMM:LastURL property.
Xmp.xmpMM.SaveID.label: Save ID

Xmp.xmpRights.Marked.desc: Indicates that this is a rights-managed resource.
Xmp.xmpRights.Marked.label: Marked

Xmp.xmpRights.Owner.desc: An unordered array specifying the legal owner(s) of a resource.
Xmp.xmpRights.Owner.label: Owner

Xmp.xmpRights.UsageTerms.desc: Text instructions on how a resource can be legally used.
Xmp.xmpRights.UsageTerms.label: Usage Terms

Xmp.xmpRights.WebStatement.desc: The location of a web page describing the owner and/or rights statement for this resource.
Xmp.xmpRights.WebStatement.label: Web Statement

Xmp.xmp.Advisory.desc: An unordered array specifying properties that were edited outside the authoring application. Each item should contain a single namespace and XPath separated by one ASCII space (U+0020).
Xmp.xmp.Advisory.label: Advisory

Xmp.xmp.BaseURL.desc: The base URL for relative URLs in the document content. If this document contains Internet links, and those links are relative, they are relative to this base URL. This property provides a standard way for embedded relative URLs to be interpreted by tools. Web authoring tools should set the value based on their notion of where URLs will be interpreted.
Xmp.xmp.BaseURL.label: Base URL

Xmp.xmp.CreateDate.desc: The date and time the resource was originally created.
Xmp.xmp.CreateDate.label: Create Date

Xmp.xmp.CreatorTool.desc: The name of the first known tool used to create the resource. If history is present in the metadata, this value should be equivalent to that of xmpMM:History's softwareAgent property.
Xmp.xmp.CreatorTool.label: Creator Tool

Xmp.xmp.Identifier.desc: An unordered array of text strings that unambiguously identify the resource within a given context. An array item may be qualified with xmpidq:Scheme to denote the formal identification system to which that identifier conforms. Note: The dc:identifier property is not used because it lacks a defined scheme qualifier and has been defined in the XMP Specification as a simple (single-valued) property.
Xmp.xmp.Identifier.label: Identifier

Xmp.xmp.Label.desc: A word or short phrase that identifies a document as a member of a user-defined collection. Used to organize documents in a file browser.
Xmp.xmp.Label.label: Label

Xmp.xmp.MetadataDate.desc: The date and time that any metadata for this resource was last changed. It should be the same as or more recent than xmp:ModifyDate.
Xmp.xmp.MetadataDate.label: Metadata Date

Xmp.xmp.ModifyDate.desc: The date and time the resource was last modified. Note: The value of this property is not necessarily the same as the file's system modification date because it is set before the file is saved.
Xmp.xmp.ModifyDate.label: Modify Date

Xmp.xmp.Nickname.desc: A short informal name for the resource.
Xmp.xmp.Nickname.label: Nickname

Xmp.xmp.Rating.desc: A number that indicates a document's status relative to other documents, used to organize documents in a file browser. Values are user-defined within an application-defined range.
Xmp.xmp.Rating.label: Rating

Xmp.xmp.Thumbnails.desc: An alternative array of thumbnail images for a file, which can differ in characteristics such as size or image encoding.
Xmp.xmp.Thumbnails.label: Thumbnails

Xmp.dc.contributor.desc: Contributors to the resource (other than the authors).
Xmp.dc.contributor.label: Contributor

Xmp.dc.coverage.desc: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
Xmp.dc.coverage.label: Coverage

Xmp.dc.creator.desc: The authors of the resource (listed in order of precedence, if significant).
Xmp.dc.creator.label: Creator

Xmp.dc.date.desc: Date(s) that something interesting happened to the resource.
Xmp.dc.date.label: Date

Xmp.dc.description.desc: A textual description of the content of the resource. Multiple values may be present for different languages.
Xmp.dc.description.label: Description

Xmp.dc.format.desc: The file format used when saving the resource. Tools and applications should set this property to the save format of the data. It may include appropriate qualifiers.
Xmp.dc.format.label: Format

Xmp.dc.identifier.desc: Unique identifier of the resource. Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
Xmp.dc.identifier.label: Identifier

Xmp.dc.language.desc: An unordered array specifying the languages used in the resource.
Xmp.dc.language.label: Language

Xmp.dc.publisher.desc: An entity responsible for making the resource available. Examples of a Publisher include a person, an organization, or a service. Typically, the name of a Publisher should be used to indicate the entity.
Xmp.dc.publisher.label: Publisher

Xmp.dc.relation.desc: Relationships to other documents. Recommended best practice is to identify the related resource by means of a string conforming to a formal identification system.
Xmp.dc.relation.label: Relation

Xmp.dc.rights.desc: Informal rights statement, selected by language. Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.
Xmp.dc.rights.label: Rights

Xmp.dc.source.desc: Unique identifier of the work from which this resource was derived.
Xmp.dc.source.label: Source

Xmp.dc.subject.desc: An unordered array of descriptive phrases or keywords that specify the topic of the content of the resource.
Xmp.dc.subject.label: Subject

Xmp.dc.title.desc: The title of the document, or the name given to the resource. Typically, it will be a name by which the resource is formally known.
Xmp.dc.title.label: Title

Xmp.dc.type.desc: A document type; for example, novel, poem, or working paper.
Xmp.dc.type.label: Type
